facts.fact: The study analyzed 62 samples of chocolates and chocolate wafers sold in Turkey.
35 samples of chocolate were categorized into various types including milk chocolate and chocolate with nuts.
Trans fatty acids in chocolate samples ranged from 0.00% to 6.23%.
The study was supported by Selcuk University Scientific Research Foundation.
27 samples of chocolate wafers were also analyzed, categorized as pure chocolate wafers and those with nuts.
